The paper discusses backoff algorithms used in distributed systems, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), distributed computing (cs.DC), networked systems (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), and performance analysis (cs.PF). The focus on the balls-into-bins problem suggests a potential connection to randomized algorithms (cs.DS) as well, but this is less likely given the emphasis on distributed systems.
